   "source": [
    "# Equation de Schrödinger et états comprimés\n",
    "\n",
    "Ce TD a pour but de simuler numériquement le TD \"Etats quantiques d’atomes de césium dans un piège harmonique\" du cours de physique quantique.\n",
    "\n",
    "On prendra $m=1$, $\\hbar=1$. On considère de plus un piège harmonique de pulsation $\\omega = 2\\pi$. \n",
    "\n",
    "1. Ecrire (avec un papier et un crayon!) l'équation de Schrödinger. \n",
    "\n",
    "2. Ecrire (avec un papier et un crayon) la fonction d'onde de l'état fondamental du piège harmonique. \n",
    "\n",
    "On va échantillonner l'espace entre -5 et 5 avec un pas de 0.02\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Ecrire une fonction Python qui calcule un état Gaussien d'écart type $\\sigma_x$ de vitesse $v_0$ et centré en $x_0$. \n",
    "\n",
    "4. Ecrire une fonction Python qui calcule le Laplacien d'une fonction d'onde $\\psi$.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. Ecrire la fonction Python `psi_prime(t, psi, V)` qui donne la dérivée de psi. Vérifier graphiquement que l'on a bien $\\frac{\\partial \\psi}{\\partial t} = -i\\frac{\\omega}{2} \\psi$ pour l'état fondamental du piège. \n",
    "\n",
    "6. Résoudre numériquement sur un temps $t=1.5$ l'équation de Schrödinger pour différents états initiaux : par exemple un paquet centré en $-2$ initialement au repos et de largeur $0.3$. On utilisera la méthode `RK23`.\n",
    "\n",
    "7. Ecrire une fonction python `moments_x(psi)` qui retourne $\\mathbb{E}(X)$ (position moyenne) et $\\mathbb{E}((X - \\mathbb{E}(X))^2)$ (carré de la largeur du paquet)\n",
    "\n",
    "8. Tracer ces moments en fonction de t.\n",
    "\n",
    "9. Question 7 et 8, mais avec l'impulsion. Dans le calcul de l'espérance, on suprimera les parties hautes impulsions qui sont dûes à du bruit numérique\n",
    "\n",
    "10. Pendant 0.5 seconde, on laisse la paquet évoluer librement (V=0) puis pendant une durée $t<0.5$, le paquet évolue avec le potentiel harmonique. Tracer la largeur en impulsion en fonction de cette durée. \n"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "501f2f54",

   },
   "source": [
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "## Solution"
   ]
  },

    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "Equation de Schrödinger : \n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "i\\hbar\\frac{\\partial\\psi}{\\partial t} = -\\frac{\\hbar^2}{2m}\\frac{\\partial^2\\psi}{\\partial x} + \\frac{1}{2} m \\omega^2 x^2\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "\n",
    "Etat fondamental : on définit $a_\\mathrm{oh} = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\hbar}{m\\omega}}$. L'état fondamental est donné par :\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "\\psi_0 =  \\frac{1}{\\left( \\pi a^2_\\mathrm{oh}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{4}}} e^{-\\frac{x^2}{2a_\\mathrm{oh}^2}}\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "\n",
    "a_ho = np.sqrt(hbar/(m*omega))\n",
    "psi_0 = gaussian_packet(a_ho, 0, 0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "1829db03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib import animation\n",
    "from IPython.display import HTML\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy import integrate\n",
    "\n",
    "from numba import jit, njit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "f43475d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Question 3\n",
    "\n",
    "L = 10.\n",
    "dx = 0.02\n",
    "N_x = int(round(L/dx))\n",
    "\n",
    "x = (np.arange(N_x)-N_x//2)*dx\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "m = 1\n",
    "hbar = 1\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "63caec1b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "def norm(psi):\n",
    "    return np.sqrt(np.sum(dx*np.abs(psi)**2))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def gaussian_packet(sigma, x_0=0, v_0=0):\n",
    "    k_x = m*v_0/hbar\n",
    "    psi = np.exp(-(x-x_0)**2 / (2.0 * sigma**2)) * np.exp(1j * k_x * x)\n",
    "    psi = psi / norm(psi)\n",
    "    return psi"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d8bd4c97",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "T = 1\n",
    "omega = 2*np.pi / T\n",
    "\n",
    "V = 0.5 * m * omega**2 * x**2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0d93814e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Question 4\n",
    "\n",
    "@jit\n",
    "def Laplace(psi, dx=dx):\n",
    "    output = np.zeros_like(psi)\n",
    "    for i in range(1, N_x-1):\n",
    "        output[i] = (psi[i-1] + psi[i+1]) - 2*psi[i]\n",
    "    output[0] = psi[1] - 2*psi[0]\n",
    "    output[-1] = psi[-2] - 2*psi[-1]\n",
    "    return output/(dx**2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "6f604f08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "1.78 µs ± 31.1 ns per loop (mean ± std. dev. of 7 runs, 1000000 loops each)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "psi = gaussian_packet(1.5, 10)\n",
    "_ = Laplace(psi)\n",
    "\n",
    "%timeit Laplace(psi)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "ec26aff4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Question 5\n",
    "def psi_prime(t, psi, V):\n",
    "    return -1j * (- 0.5 * hbar / m * Laplace(psi) + V / hbar * psi)\n",
    "psi_prime(0.0, psi, V);"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "686a490e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# On vérifie que l'on a bien un état propre\n",
    "\n",
    "a_ho = np.sqrt(hbar/(m*omega))\n",
    "psi_0 = gaussian_packet(a_ho, 0, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.abs(-1J*omega/2*psi_0)**2)\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.abs(psi_prime(0, psi_0, V))**2)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('x')\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r'$|\\psi|^2$')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "62317072",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Question 6\n",
    "\n",
    "t0 = 0.0\n",
    "tf = 1.5\n",
    "t_eval = np.linspace(t0, tf, 101)\n",
    "\n",
    "psi_0 = gaussian_packet(.3, -2, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "sol = integrate.solve_ivp(psi_prime, t_span = [t0, tf], y0 = psi_0, t_eval = t_eval, method=\"RK23\", args=(V,))"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "plt.plot(x, np.abs(psi_0)**2)\n",
    "plt.plot(x, np.abs(sol.y[:, ::5])**2);\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "25b1456b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Question 7\n",
    "def moments_x(psi):\n",
    "    proba = np.abs(psi)**2\n",
    "    norm = np.sum(proba)\n",
    "    center = np.sum(proba*x)/norm\n",
    "    var = np.sum(proba*(x-center)**2)/norm\n",
    "    return center, var\n",
    "\n",
    "centers, width = np.array([moments_x(psi) for psi in sol.y.T]).T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "# Question 8\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1, ax2 = fig.subplots(2, 1, sharex=True)\n",

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "a5ae3be5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Question 9\n",
    "\n",
    "p = np.fft.fftshift(hbar*2*np.pi*np.fft.fftfreq(len(x), d=dx))\n",
    "\n",
    "def psi_tilde(psi):\n",
    "    out = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft(psi))\n",
    "    return out\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def moments_p(psi):\n",
    "    mask = np.abs(p)<40\n",
    "    proba = np.abs(psi_tilde(psi))**2\n",
    "    norm = np.sum(proba[mask])\n",
    "    center = np.sum(proba[mask]*p[mask])/norm\n",
    "    var = np.sum(proba[mask]*(p[mask]-center)**2)/norm\n",
    "    return center, var\n",
    "\n",
    "momentum, temperature = np.array([moments_p(psi) for psi in sol.y.T]).T"
   ]
  },
